t-back-to-school-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprepared%20to%20return%20to%20school%20last%20January%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20reviewed%20our%20schedule.%20My%20fourth%20grader%20and%20kindergartener%20were%20signed%20up%20for%20the%20swim%20team%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20To%20get%20them%20to%20the%20practices%20three%20afternoons%20a%20week%2C%20I%20would%20need%20to%20stop%20working%20about%20an%20hour%20earlier%20than%20usual.%20It%20wasn't%20ideal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20can't%20they%20just%20walk%3F%26quot%3B%20The%20pool%20was%20on%20a%20college%20campus%2C%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fswiss-vs-american-parenting-differences-independence-freedom-culture-shock-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethree%20blocks%20away%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20their%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20walking%20a%20half%20mile%20to%20and%20from%20school%20every%20day.%20That's%20not%20an%20option%20for%20my%20girls%20since%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fraising-kids-small-town-new-hampshire-benefits-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20we%20live%20in%20a%20rural%20area%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20about%20a%2020-minute%20drive%20from%20town.%20Yet%20once%20they%20were%20in%20town%2C%20walking%20seemed%20like%20the%20obvious%20solution.%20My%20biggest%20hesitation%20was%20that%20no%20other%20kids%20were%20walking%20to%20practice%20despite%20how%20popular%20swimming%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ceadd764-100b-4998-abf0-3dac8f0c93b4%5C%22%3EMy%20husband%20was%20hesitant%2C%20but%20the%20girls%20were%20immediately%20excited%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20immediately%20set%20on%20the%20idea%2C%20but%20my%20husband%20wasn't%20so%20sure.%20Like%20me%2C%20he%20didn't%20have%20any%20safety%20concerns%3B%20he%20was%20just%20worried%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-stop-worrying-about-what-other-people-think-2016-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhat%20other%20people%20would%20think%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20worried%20that%20our%209-year-old%20would%20be%20fine%2C%20but%20our%205-year-old%20might%20cause%20trouble.%20But%20we%20know%20our%20kids%20and%20ultimately%20felt%20very%20sure%20our%20youngest%20would%20follow%20her%20big%20sister's%20lead%20during%20the%20walk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20my%20husband%20on%20board%2C%20I%20talked%20with%20my%20daughters.%20They%20were%20immediately%20excited%20about%20the%20idea.%20They%20love%20going%20places%20directly%20after%20school%2C%20and%20the%20novelty%20of%20a%20walk%20with%20no%20adults%20was%20appealing.%20Eventually%20I%20told%20the%20school%20the%20girls%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bwalkers.%26quot%3B%20I%20prepared%20for%20questions%20or%20pushback%20but%20didn't%20get%20any.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e86b2e39-976e-4dca-b685-4b42fd614230%5C%22%3EWe%20prepped%20the%20girls%20with%20lots%20of%20safety%20instructions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20girls%20started%20walking%2C%20we%20went%20over%20logistics.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-netflix-tv-show-old-enough-causes-among-parents%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWe%20mapped%20the%20possible%20routes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20when%20the%20girls%20chose%20one%20that%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20selected%2C%20I%20had%20to%20bite%20my%20tongue%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20up%20to%20them.%20We%20covered%20crosswalk%20safety%20and%20made%20them%20promise%20to%20stay%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20emphasized%20that%20help%20was%20always%20nearby%20if%20they%20needed%20it.%20It's%20important%20to%20me%20that%20they%20feel%20safe%20in%20our%20community%20and%20know%20that%20they%20can%20count%20on%20our%20neighbors%20%E2%80%94%20even%20the%20ones%20they've%20never%20met.%20I%20reminded%20them%20that%20they%20could%20always%20go%20back%20to%20school%2C%20into%20the%20police%20station%20along%20the%20route%2C%20or%20into%20the%20college%20athletic%20center%20and%20ask%20to%20use%20the%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20assured%20the%20girls%20they%20could%20do%20this%2C%20but%20they%20didn't%20need%20to%20hear%20that%20%E2%80%94%20they%20weren't%20worried%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221eb7e748-8fb3-4587-9880-108cf0259496%5C%22%3EFour%20families%20were%20walking%20by%20the%20end%20of%20swim%20practice%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20first%20day%20of%20swim%20I%20finished%20work%20and%20headed%20to%20the%20pool.%20I%20held%20my%20breath%20as%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-family-living-in-netherlands-new-perspective-on-modesty-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewent%20into%20the%20locker%20room%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20breathed%20a%20sigh%20of%20relief%20when%20I%20saw%20both%20girls%20changed%20for%20swimming%20and%20having%20a%20snack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDid%20they%20walk%3F%26quot%3B%20another%20mom%20asked%20me%20at%20pickup.%20She%20wasn't%20sure%20if%20her%20two%20daughters%20could%20handle%20the%20walk%2C%20but%20soon%2C%20they%20were%20asking%20to%20walk%20with%20my%20kids.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20swim%20season%2C%20four%20sets%20of%20siblings%20were%20walking%20from%20school%20to%20practice.%20I%20have%20no%20idea%20if%20that%20happened%20because%20I%20was%20the%20one%20to%20break%20the%20ice%2C%20but%20it%20was%20really%20heartening%20to%20see%20more%20kids%20walking%20independently.%20The%20kids%20loved%20it%20so%20much%20that%20they%20chose%20walking%20over%20a%20ride%2C%20even%20on%20the%20coldest%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20so%20many%20fond%20memories%20from%20walking%20to%20and%20from%20school%2C%20whether%20chatting%20with%20the%20crossing%20guard%2C%20making%20up%20silly%20games%2C%20or%20just%20exploring%20with%20friends.%20Walking%20to%20swim%20gave%20my%20kids%2C%20and%20eventually%20their%20friends%2C%20the%20unsupervised%2C%20independent%20space%20to%20have%20similar%20experiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20